# Trivy ignore file — read by release.yml's Trivy scans.
# Each entry MUST have a justification and an owner/date so it never becomes a silent forever-suppression.

# CVE-2026-4867 — path-to-regexp ReDoS (Denial of Service).
# Location: express@4 -> path-to-regexp@0.1.12 (transitive, api image only).
# Why ignored (not patched): the published fix is 0.1.13 (Express-4 0.1.x line), but forcing it via
#   an npm override causes npm to hoist 0.1.13 over the path-to-regexp@8.x that NestJS's OpenAPI
#   generator needs (it calls pathToRegexp.parse, which the 0.1.x line lacks) — breaking `openapi:gen`.
#   The real fix is migrating Express 4 -> 5 (uses path-to-regexp@8.x, no ReDoS), tracked as a
#   separate follow-up. Risk here is low: it's a ReDoS in route-pattern parsing on an admin API that
#   sits behind Oathkeeper auth, with fixed (non-user-controlled) route definitions.
# Added: 2026-06-21. Revisit with the Express 5 migration.
CVE-2026-4867
